{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696386/1930092501/0394.xml":{"full_text":"28\nThree Furnishings\n\u2019Essential\nFamily life should center\nin the living room, Helen\n\u25a0Townsend Barton, nationa.l\nauthority, sets\nforth m a .discussion o\u00a3\nhofhe arrangement in ner\nlatest book. \u201cWhen Good\nFurnishings Get Together,\ncopies of which have been\nreceived by local furniture\ndealers in connection with\nthe Home Furnishings Style\nShow.\n\u201cGuests should find a\nfriendly greeting m the\nliving room where iamiiy\nlife should center,\u201d Miss\nBarton writes. \u201cThus this\nroom has a double responsi\nbility. Its arrangement\nmust minister to the needs\nof every member of the\nhome circle, and at the same\ntime must be ever ready to\nextend hospitality to call\ners\u2014to convey an impres\nsion that makes your words\nof welcome ring true.\nFirst\nConversational\nGroup\n\u201cIn the arrangement of\na living room, the show place\nof the home, there- should\nbe three furnishings\u2014con-\nversational, reading and\nwriting. In smaller rooms,\nperhaps, the first two may\nbe combined, or the second\nand third. The minimum\nnumber of pieces for any\ngroup is three: A chair,\ntable and lamp. Other pieces\nmay be added \u2014but never\nhave less.\n\u201cArrange first the conver\nsational group, with daven\nport or love seat, armchairs\nand occasional chairs, and\nthe essential tables and\nlamps. This group may\nhave as its center of in\nterest a fireplace, or a pair\nof French windows, a radio,\nor an impressive piece of\nfurniture. Pieces should be\nclose enough together so\nthat conversation can be\nneighborly.\nThen The\nReading Group\n\u201cThen plan the reading\ngroup\u2014one or two comfort\nable chairs with a lamp and\ntable for books, magazines\nand smoking accessories.\nMaybe this will be \u2018Dad\u2019s\ncorner,\u2019 in which case select\na big, mannish lounge chair,\nwith or without an ottoman.\nWhenever two chairs are\nused in a group, remember\nto use contrasting types.\n\u201cOne chair may be a\nlarge overstuffed; the other\na less massive, though com\nfortable chain Where there\nis a youngster in the family,\none of the new small-size\narm chairs will add a\npiquant touch to the room.\nFinally Writing\nGroup\n\u201cA writing group is a\npractical addition to any\nliving room. In desk styles\nthere is almost limitless\nchoice \u2014the colonial, Span\nish, kneehole, secretary and\nkidney types are among the\nmost popular. For a room\nwithout a fireplace, the\nwriting group may be made\nthe center of interest by\nadding a tall pier-case on\neither sidfc of the low desk,\nusing the upper shelves for\ncolorful bric-a-brac.\n\u201cNone of the groups\nshould be shut off from the\nrest of the room. Set them\nout in \u2018L\u2019 or \u2018U\u2019 shapes,\nwith the open part facing\nmore or less toward the cen\nter of the room. This not\nonly makes each piece more\naccessible, but also tends to\nkeep the room as a unit.\u201d\nBeauty\nIn Black Glass\nAmong the many beauti\nful things to be purchased\nin glassware are the plates,\nbowls, glasses and candle\nsticks in black glasS. They\ngive the table an unusually\ninteresting appearance and\n\u00a3itrast strikingly with the\nen and the silver?\nFamily Life Centers in the Living Rdotn-'\nA Beautiful Living Room Ensemble\nft r 1 \u25a0MM F\n|j ril g L\n1\nItalian and Early English Alcove showing the design of furniture, rugs and decorations suitable for\nthe English type architecture K which is so pupular around Washington. Displayed at W. B. Moses.\nPractically everything now\non display in local furniture\nstores represents the latest\nin fashion. Therefore, the\nlocal dealers point out, the\npublic will-be able not only\nto buy furnishings that are\nfashionable but at prices\nwhich, while low, will be\nmaintained at their present\nlevels.\nInventories have been low\nfor some time, due partly\nto the fact that the business\ndepression which the coun\ntry recently experienced\ncaused merchants to buy\ncautiously and because mer\nchants were preparing to\nrestock for a complete new\nline of goods for fall show\ning.\nConsidering all these fac\ntors, the local dealers ex\nplain, the dates for the\nHome Furnishings Style\nShow are opportune, advan\ntageous both for the public\nand the merchant alike.\nI\nRugs and Carpets\nMust Be\nHarmonious\nRugs and carpets can no\nlonger be considered with\nout regard to the furnish\nings of the room, according\nto Miss Helen Townsend\nBarton, authority on home\nfurnishings.\n\u201cThe time has passed,\u201d\nMiss Barton said, \u201cwhen\nwomen bought a\u2019rug solely\nbecause they liked it, and\ndid not think of it as part\nof the decoration scheme of\nthe room in which it was to\ngo. Women now realize that\ninfinitely more satisfying re\nsults may be obtained by\nthe selection of just the\nright rug.\n\u201cThere is a great demand\nnow for highly decorative\nrugs. For a long time we\nhave been using the plain,\nneutral tone carpets, but\nfor large rooms we are be\nginning to appreciate the\ncolor and decoration which\ncan be introduced through\nthe use of figured carpets.\nEven in unfigured carpets\nwe are going in for livelier\ncolors. Tones running from\ncerise and spring green to\nrich orange and deep laven\nders are now available.\n\u201cThe heavy old English\nstyles now so popular de\nmand the rich subdued\ntones of dull reds; the\nequally popular eighteenth\ncentury designs\u2019 are most\nhappily used on rugs of\nlight and delicate colons\nLatest Furniture Fashions; Lowest\nPrices in Years Now\nBeing Shown\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES\n\u201cFor the spacious room\nthe figured designs are ap\npropriate. Rugs and car\npets which are strongly\nmarked with patterns in\nbold and vigorous colors\nfind their place in the large\nroom where somewhat mas\nsive and sturdy furniture is\nused. They make the cor\nrect background for heavily\ncarved pieces of Spanish,\n\u2014Make your home a cheery place,\nwhere your friends like to gather!\n\u2014Furniture carefully selected and\ncorrectly placed creates the atmos\nphere!\nPresenting New\nFashions in Home\nFurnishings\nI\n\nDo You Know?\ni That there is one\nof the leading fur\nniture stores lo\ncated in South\nB/n 'Km west Washington,\nwhose business\nhas been built on\nfl zFljTli strictly satisfied\ncustomers. We\ncarry all the lead\nfl T f n nationally\nJ V I A known makes of\nII J high-grade furni\nture and rugs. By\nbuying in carload\nlots, coupled with our low overhead, due to\nlocation, saves you money. For over 30 years\nwe have served the people of Washington.\nVisit our store during\nSTYLE SHOW WEEK\nand you will be amazed at the remarkable\nvalues offered.\nWm. E. Miller\nFurniture Co., Inc.\nI\n7thandES.W. 3140MSt.N.W.\nCourtesy and Service\u2014Our Motto\nItalian or Jacobean furni\nture.\n\u201cSolid colors, small all\nover patterns, or indistinct,\ndelicate designs are the best\nselection for the small room\nwhere furniture of light and\ngraceful line is used. The\ndelicacy of the furniture re\nquires a floor covering in\nkeeping with it. Added zest\nmay be secured in the room\nwhere the plain tone carpet\nis used by placing on it\nseveral small rugs, carefully\nselected to heighten the\ndecorative' scheme of the\nroom.\u201d\nTha National Dally\nOld Masters\nRetained\nAccording to General\nChairman J. P. Herrman, of\nthe Furniture Style Show.\n\u201cModern methods of man-\n__\nThe \u201cNATIONAL\u201d Says:\nHome Hearts Are the\nHappiest!\n/N CONJUNCTION with other Washington merchants who are engaged in trying to promote\nbetter homes through the use of better home furnishings, The \u201cNATIONAL\u201d Furniture Com\npany, a link in America's largest chain of furniture stores, is pleased to announce its participation in\nthe premiere of The National Home Furnishing Style Show.\nThe \u201cNATIONAL\u201d takes this opportunity to extend an invitation to the general public to visit\nthis big institution, where \u201cBetter Values, Better Terms, Better Service\u201d mean more than a slogan\n\u2014and inspect the newest and finest in furniture, priced to accommodate all.\nfl Ii Im I I fl li I\ni war bm\nThis 4-Piece Walnut Veneer Bedroom Suite\nHas Beautiful Mahogany Overlays\nzf remarkable value in fine bedroom furniture is here presented for the first\ntime. The straight-end Bed, dainty Vanity, graceful Chest of Drawers with\ndeck and large Dresser are artistically constructed of fine cabinet woods, hand- I\nsomely carved, decorated and high-lighted. Without further words, won\u2019t you JL VZ\ndrop in and really SEE this unusual value? Convenient terms may be ar\nranged.\nr|\u2014- r\u2014\nC lUIUI/\nA Genuine Kroehler Bed-Davenport Suite\nIn a Beautiful Mohair Cover\nA living rbom by day, a bedroom by night; thus does this double-duty\nKROEHLER suite convert one room to the purposes of two. Upholstered in\nhandsome Mohair, with loose spring seat cushions, the three pieces of this n\nsuite are constructed to give years of satisfactory service. Bed-Davenport, B\nwhich opens into full-size bed,'button-back Bunny Chair and Comfy Arm\nChair. Convenient terms may be arranged.\nTERMS SERVICE\nOur 'll-\no r,d FA V BBSB 111 or\nL I I I I 1 I W VOVf\nfl F I I I I J r tht\ntmnll J W\nth t h\u00abianc\u00bb\nor IUI I I 111 WI 1\nmonthly\nto ,u, t\natidrd AiaPjf\u00df S K on vour Our\n'or L A r o-uc\u00ab\u00ab deliver to\npriviieoee on\nthree advertieed and Viraleid.\nitems.\ni .ii i\nTHURSDAY, SEPTEMBER SB, 1080\nufacture and modern ideas\nof comfoft have made pos\nsible great improvements in\nfurniture in the past years\nand while the beauty of\nline and proportion of the\ndesigns of the old masters\nhas been retained many im-\nprovements for greater com\nfort have been made.\u201d\nMr. Herrman said the\nGeorgian styles are very\npopular at this time and so\nare the provincial, peasant\nand early English and early\nAmerican designs. The early\nEnglish styles are probably\nmore popular than they\nhave ever been before and\nthe French Provincial and\nthe Swedish Peasant are\nrecommended because of\ntheir charm and simplicity.","height":"30341","width":"24232"}}
